(thirdQuint)Transcutaneous Posterior Tibial Nerve Stimulation for Treatment of Chronic Anal Fissure.

 Sacral nerve stimulation has been recently tried for management of chronic anal fissure with promising results.

 However, the technique described is invasive with the need for surgically implantable expensive stimulator electrodes.

 The aim of this study was to evaluate the efficacy of posterior tibial nerve stimulation (PTN) by transcutaneous electrical nerve stimulation (TENS) and to compare it to the conventional LIS.

 This non-invasive technique has been proved to be of acceptable results in treatment of fecal incontinence and urinary incontinence.

